      "body" : "The behavior is a bit kludgy, but that's there to un-export PKG_CONFIG_LIBDIR, since we export it for OSX (to help with finding brew paths). Exporting a new var breaks autoconf's caching because the env looks different before/after, and that causes all kinds of wonky problems.\r\n\r\nNo clue why this would upset CentOS. I suppose we could guard that path so that we only unset what we ourselves export.",
